Primary Tumor Sites

Source: ../vignettes/primary_tumor_sites.Rmd
primary_tumor_sites.Rmd

PCGR integrates a variety of different datasets, that typically use different notations or ontologies when it comes to diseases or phenotypes. We have cross-referenced a variety of ontologies (DiseaseOntology, EFO, OncoTree, UMLS) in use in the oncology domain, and organized all the various tumor subtypes into 30 different main tumor sites (see also https://github.com/sigven/oncoPhenoMap).

Below you can browse all the various phenotype terms that are associated with each of the primary sites. This as a guide to choose the primary tumor type when running PCGR for a given sample (option --tumor_site).



Developed by Sigve Nakken, Peter Diakumis.

Site built with pkgdown 2.0.2.
